VA melodious duet
p3
sVnews
p4
VSaptaswara and Thyagaraya Ganasabha jointly organised a violin duet by Peri Sriramamurthy and his son Thyagaraju, at Sabha&#8217;s premises last week. Saptswara is a new music sabha launched by Balamurali&#8217;s disciple Balakrishna Sastryto promote young artistes and celebrate the contribution of great personalities from Carnatic and Hindustani styles.A violin concert by father-son duo was presented at Thyagaraya Gana Sabha premises to mark the 92nd Jayanthi of Ustad Bismillah Khan, who had a great association with Hyderabad music circles. This was a first-of-its-kind function organised by any music sabha in Hyderabad after this recipient of &#8216;Bharat Ratna&#8217; passed away.The violin players accompanied by D.S.R.Murthy on mridangam and Ghantasala Satyasai on morsing brought back memories of the shahnai melodies of Bismillah Khan, while presenting a similarragain Carnatic and Hindustani. The Peri duo opened with Natakuranjivarnamand presented it briskly in Tisra Pai Kalam and received instant applause.
